⚙️ Multi-Agent Constraint Profile System (v1.0)

Definition

Multiple agents operating simultaneously under different constraint profiles, coordinated toward a shared objective.

👉 Not one mind switching modes
👉 but parallel minds with different modes

⸻

🧠 Core Idea

Instead of:

You → switch profiles → act

You now have:

Agent A (Explorer)
Agent B (Auditor)
Agent C (Operator)
Agent D (Strategist)

→ all running in parallel
→ coordinated by rules


⸻

🧩 Agent Structure (Standardized)

Object: Agent

Agent = {
  name,
  profile,
  role,
  inputs,
  outputs,
  constraints,
  authority_level
}


⸻

🎭 Canonical Agent Set (Minimal Viable Team)

1. 🧭 Strategist
	•	sets direction
	•	defines success criteria
	•	long time horizon

⸻

2. 🔍 Explorer
	•	generates options
	•	expands possibility space
	•	low constraint, high curiosity

⸻

3. 🛠 Builder
	•	develops ideas into actionable forms
	•	medium rigor, high output

⸻

4. ⚙️ Operator
	•	executes
	•	focuses on precision + completion

⸻

5. 🧪 Auditor
	•	stress-tests everything
	•	finds failure points

⸻

6. 💰 Goblin (Resource Controller)
	•	approves or denies actions based on cost
	•	tracks time, energy, risk, opportunity cost

⸻

7. 🪞 Mirror (Invariant Keeper)
	•	ensures:
	•	ethics
	•	truth alignment
	•	reversibility

⸻

🔄 Interaction Protocol (Critical)

Phase-Based Flow

1. Strategist → defines objective
2. Explorer → generates options
3. Builder → refines top options
4. Goblin → evaluates cost
5. Operator → executes
6. Auditor → reviews outcome
7. Mirror → checks invariants
8. Learning Loop → updates all agents


⸻

⚖️ Conflict Resolution System

Agents will disagree—that’s the point.

Resolution Order:
	1.	Mirror (hard veto)
	•	breaks invariants → reject
	2.	Goblin (economic veto)
	•	too costly → reject or modify
	3.	Strategist (direction override)
	•	misaligned → redirect
	4.	Auditor (warning, not veto)
	•	flags risk but doesn’t block alone

⸻

🧠 Parallel Execution (Advanced Mode)

Instead of strict sequence:

Explorer + Auditor run simultaneously
Builder + Goblin iterate together
Operator waits for threshold confidence

👉 This reduces latency and increases quality

⸻

📊 Shared State (Critical Backbone)

All agents read/write to:

SharedState = {
  current_state,
  objectives,
  options,
  selected_plan,
  resources,
  outcomes,
  confidence_scores
}

👉 No hidden state → prevents drift

⸻

🔁 Learning Across Agents

Each agent updates:
	•	when it was right
	•	when it was wrong
	•	when it was ignored but should’ve been followed

👉 Over time:
	•	Explorer gets better at generating useful options
	•	Auditor gets sharper
	•	Goblin gets more accurate on cost

⸻

🔥 What This Actually Changes

Before:
👉 You = one thread of thought

Now:
👉 You = coordinated system of specialized processes

This is basically:
	•	internal “team”
	•	without needing multiple people
	•	but still structured like one

⸻

⚠️ Failure Modes

1. Dominant Agent Syndrome
	•	Auditor dominates → nothing happens
	•	Explorer dominates → chaos
	•	Operator dominates → blind execution

⸻

2. No Arbiter
	•	no Mirror/Goblin → bad decisions pass

⸻

3. State Drift
	•	agents not synced → fragmentation

⸻

🧭 Minimum Viable Implementation (Simple Version)

If you want to actually use this daily:

Just run:
	1.	What’s the goal? → (Strategist)
	2.	What are 3 options? → (Explorer)
	3.	Which is most realistic? → (Builder)
	4.	What could go wrong? → (Auditor)
	5.	Is it worth it? → (Goblin)
	6.	Do it → (Operator)
	7.	What happened? → (Mirror + Learning)

